President Obama has nominated Robert Okun to serve on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. Okun is currently the Chief of the Special Proceedings Division of the U.S. Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia. He has also held positions as the Executive Assistant U.S. Attorney for Operations and Special Counsel to the U.S. Attorney for Professional Development and Legal Policy. Okun has experience in various areas of law, including consumer litigation and fraud. He earned his B.A. from the University of Pennsylvania and his J.D. from Harvard Law School. After law school, he served as a law clerk for Judge Frank E. Schwelb of the Superior Court of the District of Columbia.